		<text>
		<body>
		<pb n="1"/>
		
			<p><hi rend="underline">Hebrew</hi></p>									
		  <p rend="indent(10)"><date>Adar 1842 &#40;or 1847&#41;</date></p>
		  <p rend="indent(10)"><placeName>Savannah</placeName></p>
		  <p rend="indent(1)">Peace and every good to my honorable<lb/> friend etc. etc.</p>
		  <p rend="indent(1)">I want to announce to you&#44; my dear and<lb/> honorable friend that I <del>have</del> received your letter<lb/> last <date>Friday</date>&#44; and was exceedingly happy.  You<lb/> may send the Pentateuchs in any way you like<lb/> if only they reach the two brothers whose name<lb/> I have already given you&#59; <persName><sic>Rebbi</sic> Nahum</persName><lb/> and <persName><sic>Rebbi</sic> Jacob Leib</persName> of the city of <placeName>Shliss&#8211;<lb/>shik</placeName> in <placeName>Poland</placeName>.</p>
		  <p rend="indent(1)">I very much regret the misfortune that<lb/> has befallen you&#44; about which I read in the<lb/> Occident.  But I know nothing with which<lb/> to comfort you.  You know that it is of god.<lb/>  As our sages said&#44; &#34;A man does not move<lb/> his finger etc....and who can say<lb/> to Him &#39;What do you do&#63;&#39;&#34;&#44; May God<lb/> free you from every evil&#44; and may He fulfill<lb/> all his desires.  Such is the wish of your<lb/> friend.  Asher.....<persName role="author">Miles hower</persName></p>
		  <p rend="indent(1)">over</p>
		<pb n="2"/>
		
			<p><hi rend="underline">The P.S. in Yiddish&#45;German</hi></p>
		  <p rend="indent(1)">With regard to what you have written me<lb/> about your books&#44; I spoke to <persName>Mr. Eckman</persName><lb/> He told me that he had sold some&#44; and<lb/> that you will shortly hear from him.<lb/>  You may send the Occident to <persName>Taivel<lb/> Rosenbund</persName>.  I shall continue to<lb/> use my best efforts in your service.</p>
		</body>
	</text>
